description:
Files: runtime/src/yield_flag.rs (new), runtime/src/heap.rs, src/runtime.rs

New file:
  #[no_mangle]
  pub static FZ_SHOULD_YIELD: std::sync::atomic::AtomicU8 = AtomicU8::new(0);

Global (not per-process) because: (a) native Tail-CC JIT fns have no cheap path to current process; (b) external timer/signal handler can write to a known address without knowing which process is running — foundation for future soft preemption.

In Heap::alloc(), after bump:
  if self.bump_top >= self.gc_watermark {
      FZ_SHOULD_YIELD.store(1, Ordering::Relaxed);
  }
Existing note_alloc_pressure()/pressure AtomicBool unchanged (park-time path).

Clear FZ_SHOULD_YIELD in run_until_idle before CURRENT_PROCESS install, and in park_time_gc after any gc() call.

Tests: crossing watermark sets global; store(0) clears it; existing pressure-flag tests pass.
